    <h3 class="panel-title">Case Control Structure</h3>
    <p>You have been given a function where an object which may or may not be of the below mentioned type is sent as an argument. You have to use the case control structure in Ruby to identify the class to which the object belongs and print the following output:

    if Hacker, output "It's a Hacker!"
    if Submission, output "It's a Submission!"
    if TestCase, output "It's a TestCase!"
    if Contest, output "It's a Contest!"
    for any other object, output "It's an unknown model"</p>
